The paper discusses the design and implementation of a key-value store for write-heavy applications, which falls under the category of database systems (cs.DB) and distributed systems (cs.DC). The paper also mentions the use of a single thread per partition executing mode, which relates to operating systems (cs.OS) and system architecture (cs.SY). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.DB and cs.DC, followed by cs.OS, cs.SY, and cs.DS (data structures) as a possible sub-category within cs.DB.
